## Edge cases

- **Face rig has no blendshapes:** EMOCA / DECA / FACSHuman all assume blendshape
  or FLAME mesh output. 2D portrait without blendshapes is out of scope — route to
  `/lip-sync` for what mouth-only animation can do.
- **Discrete-emotion-only spec:** user wants only Ekman 6. Allow it but write a
  warning: "discrete-emotion deployments cap out at scripted-character quality;
  dialog feels robotic. We recommend at least adding back-channel beats." Capture
  this in CONTROL-SURFACE.md.
- **Cultural mismatch:** user picked "high-arousal positive" for a Japanese formal
  context — over-smiling avatar. Flag, recommend the cultural display-rule overlay
  with arousal-damping.
- **Sign-language context overlap:** non-manual features in sign (brow raise =
  question marker, mouth-shape MM = "duration") are LINGUISTIC. They live in
  `/avatar-sign`. Do NOT fold them into this surface — sign NMFs override
  emotion-driven brow/mouth movements.
- **Trust-calibration on a hallucinating model:** if the underlying LLM is known
  to hallucinate confidently, exposing model-confidence to the expression layer
  helps but doesn't fix the underlying problem. Flag in EMOTION-MODEL.md.
- **Real-time + diffusion-based expression model:** doesn't exist commonly;
  regression models (EMOCA / DECA) are real-time-feasible; diffusion is offline.
- **License conflict:** EMOCA license has changed over versions; verify before
  recommending for commercial.
- **Hall's TSL teaching avatar:** mixed Thai-English content, teaching context.
  Recommend: EMOCA v2 + full 4-layer surface (V-A + back-channel-heavy beats for
  teaching + recognition micro-expressions + FACS composer) + cultural override
  for Thai politeness + trust-calibration enabled. NOTE: the sign-performing path
  uses different non-manual features driven by `/avatar-sign`; this surface is for
  the spoken-Thai-English mode only.

